Subject: Re: [VB] Electrical Problem

I had a similar issue in my 67 riviera.   I bumped some wires at the 9 pin 
box when installing the kick panel..   I took the kick panel off, and wiggled 
the wires at the 9 pin box, I think 2 had touched or something, and then it was 
fine.
  the headlights do have something that runs through the 9 pin box, so I see 
a connection there.  Check your high beam light on the dash is grounded 
(wiggle socket)  and works properly.
yes, check that all you turn signals work properly.        

